rComments: Took her class at SFSU, and quite enjoyed it. She's one of the nicests professors I've ever had, and she definitely loves the subject she teaches. Speak up in class, do the reading, and study for the two tests and you'll get an A.

I took Katie's Women and Media class at SFSU and she is truly amazing. A wonderful, passionate, intelligent professor and all around great person. I highly recommend taking anything and everything she teaches!

Taking her at SFSU; great professor! Her class is informative, organized and fun. She follows syllabus and is very clear about what she expects. Attendance is mandatory so GO TO CLASS! If you show up, do readings (which aren't a lot) and participate you will get a good grade. She is nice, helpful and engages you in her lectures. I recommend her : )

I take her class at SFSU. I LOVE THIS CLASS. I used to hate any sort of history, but she always engages the class and makes it very enjoyable. I highly recommend this class. She makes all the requirements crystal clear. Though I recommend reading what is assigned, as long as you pay attention in class, you should be fine. :) Also, she's very sweet.

LOVE her!  You have a lot of reading, but you get into groups and go over the reading, then go over it as a whole class. By the time you get to the midterm and final, you know everything and don't even have to put more than an hours worth of studying. She will go out of her way to help you with anything class related. I completely recommend her.

Katie is a good teacher, she is kind of figgity and strict. There is a LOT of reading to do, but it doesn't really matter if you do it. All you do everyday is get into groups and talk about the readings. Overall pretty easy, but boring
